The paper discusses the challenges of scaling relational databases and the emergence of NewSQL and NoSQL databases, which are all related to database systems (cs.DB). The paper also proposes a new system called Synergy that uses a specialized concurrency control system on top of a NoSQL database, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the trade-offs between write performance, disk utilization, and query expressiveness, which are related to programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE).
